# React Native / Expo Standards

- **Components**: Always use functional components + hooks. No class components.
- **Expo**: Prefer Expo APIs over bare React Native when possible (expo-router, expo-secure-store, etc.).
- **Navigation**: Use expo-router for file-based navigation; no react-navigation unless specified.
- **Styling**: Use NativeWind (Tailwind for RN) with utility classes; avoid StyleSheet.create unless for dynamic styles. Use cn() or className merging.
- **Views**: Use `<View>`, `<Text>`, `<ScrollView>`, `<FlatList>` correctly; add flex-1, safe area insets via SafeAreaView or expo-safe-area-context.
- **Performance**: Avoid unnecessary re-renders (use memo, useCallback, useMemo); profile with Flipper or React DevTools; prefer Hermes engine.
- **Accessibility**: Add accessible=true, accessibilityLabel, accessibilityHint; support VoiceOver/TalkBack.
- **State**: Prefer Zustand, Jotai, or React Query for data; no heavy Redux unless complex.
- **Types**: Strict TypeScript; use infer for props, avoid any.
- **Testing**: Suggest Detox or Jest + @testing-library/react-native for E2E/unit tests.
- **Platform**: Use Platform.OS checks sparingly; prefer cross-platform solutions.
- **Clean code**: Small files/components (<300 lines), single responsibility, remove dead code/logs.
